Kofi Annan has passed away but his passion and wise words will continue to give guidance when it is needed The family and the Kofi Annan Foundation confirmed that the globally acclaimed leader passed away in the morning on Saturday, 18 August 2018, after a short illness. Annan was a Ghanaian diplomat who served as the seventh Secretary-General of the United Nations from January 1997 to December 2006. Annan and the UN were the co-recipients of the 2001 Nobel Peace Prize. Here are some of his most inspiring quotes: 